This project explores how palm-based multimodal feedback can simulate directional “Qi” flow in VR Tai Chi practice.

## Research Question
How can multimodal cues such as vibration, airflow and EMG-triggered timing support embodied movement perception in XR?

## System Design
The system integrates Unity-based interaction logic, hand tracking on Meta Quest 3 / VIVE XR Elite, serial JSON communication, and ESP32-controlled haptic devices.

## Interaction
Recognized gestures such as Raise, Close, Push, Peng, and Ji are mapped to directional haptic output patterns.

## Technical Stack
- Unity
- XR hand tracking
- ESP32 C3 / S3
- Serial JSON protocol
- EMG threshold-based control

## Current Status
Prototype completed and under iterative refinement for interaction tuning and evaluation.
